    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-6" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#6 · $0–$120/MO · FREE TIER AVAILABLE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Buffer — Best social media scheduling automation</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For small businesses that need to schedule social posts across multiple platforms without a social media manager.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Buffer is the cleanest social scheduling tool in this list. You queue posts across Instagram, LinkedIn, Facebook, X, Pinterest, and TikTok from one calendar. The free plan handles 3 channels and 10 queued posts per channel. For small businesses manually scheduling social content, Buffer cuts the time in half. The limitation: you still have to write the content yourself.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>The cleanest social scheduling UI in the market — queue management, calendar view, analytics</h4><p>Faster than posting natively on each platform. Saves 2–3 hours/week for active social accounts.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Free plan covers 3 channels and 10 posts per channel — enough for most small businesses</h4><p>The free tier is genuinely functional, not a crippled trial.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Best-time suggestions and engagement analytics on paid plans</h4><p>Know which posts drive clicks and which fall flat, by platform.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: you still have to write every post yourself</h4><p>Buffer schedules. It doesn't create. If content creation is your bottleneck, theStacc automates that entire layer.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
