      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#9 · $16–$59/MO · FREE TRIAL AVAILABLE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Omnisend — Best e-commerce email and SMS automation</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For Shopify and WooCommerce stores that need abandoned cart, post-purchase, and SMS flows built specifically for e-commerce.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Omnisend is purpose-built for e-commerce. The abandoned cart sequence, post-purchase upsell flows, and SMS alerts are pre-built and ready to activate in minutes. Deep native integrations with Shopify and WooCommerce mean product blocks, discount codes, and order data flow automatically into emails. Not for service businesses — built purely for product sellers.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Pre-built e-commerce flows — abandoned cart, welcome series, win-back — activate in minutes</h4><p>No workflow building required. Turn them on, connect your store, done.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>SMS + email + push in one platform — unified e-commerce messaging</h4><p>Coordinate the cart recovery sequence across all three channels from one tool.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Deep Shopify and WooCommerce integration — product data flows automatically</h4><p>No manual product imports. Emails auto-populate with the right product images, prices, and links.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: no value for service businesses — built entirely for product e-commerce</h4><p>If you're a dentist, HVAC company, or SaaS, Omnisend's e-commerce focus makes it the wrong tool entirely.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

