        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">MailerLite is the leanest email tool in this list. The editor is clean and fast. Automation workflows are simpler than ActiveCampaign but more visual than Brevo. The free plan supports 1,000 subscribers and 12,000 emails/month — the most generous free tier for list size in this category. If your only need is a professional email newsletter without complexity, MailerLite gets out of your way.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Most generous free tier by list size — 1,000 subscribers free</h4><p>Double Mailchimp's 500-contact limit. Ideal for growing lists on a zero budget.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Fastest drag-and-drop email builder in the test group</h4><p>Emails go from blank to published in under 20 minutes for non-designers.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Affordable paid plans — $9–$18/month keeps it accessible for micro-businesses</h4><p>No sticker shock when you grow past the free tier.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: automation depth is limited — no behavioral scoring or CRM</h4><p>Good for newsletters. Too shallow for complex multi-step behavioral sequences. Graduates move to ActiveCampaign.</p></div></li>
